1
00:00:00,108 --> 00:00:01,980
I think it’s better for both of us

2
00:00:02,127 --> 00:00:04,059
if I stay true to my feelings.

3
00:00:04,810 --> 00:00:06,625
Forgive! Forgive!

4
00:00:06,668 --> 00:00:07,380
Well?

5
00:00:07,630 --> 00:00:08,696
Will you forgive me?

6
00:00:09,140 --> 00:00:09,804
Mm.

7
00:00:11,785 --> 00:00:14,395
Didn’t you think to tell me
your ankle was hurting?

8
00:00:14,423 --> 00:00:16,050
So when are you making me a new playlist?

9
00:00:16,110 --> 00:00:17,897
When I’m in the mood.

10
00:00:18,020 --> 00:00:19,770
You said I was your number one actor.

11
00:00:19,985 --> 00:00:21,937
You were my number one too.

12
00:00:23,807 --> 00:00:25,050
Jack, I…

13
00:00:25,137 --> 00:00:26,142
Say no more.

14
00:00:27,190 --> 00:00:28,268
I forgive you.

15
00:00:40,106 --> 00:00:41,702
When did you move here?

16
00:00:44,171 --> 00:00:45,300
Yesterday.

17
00:00:46,357 --> 00:00:50,577
I’m thinking of
a mid-century modern decor.

18
00:00:50,604 --> 00:00:51,598
What do you think?

19
00:00:54,096 --> 00:00:55,299
You’ve got good taste.

20
00:00:56,011 --> 00:00:59,140
Just in case you want to move in with me.

21
00:01:01,149 --> 00:01:03,001
I’ll put the bookshelf over there.

22
00:01:04,770 --> 00:01:06,600
The record player over here.

23
00:01:07,241 --> 00:01:11,401
And your scriptwriting desk
will go right there.

24
00:01:20,830 --> 00:01:22,520
I don’t think I’ll move in.

25
00:01:55,720 --> 00:01:58,200
I don’t belong here by your side.

26
00:02:04,598 --> 00:02:07,902
Then what are we supposed to be now?

27
00:02:23,785 --> 00:02:27,939
How about we go back
to being real friends?

28
00:02:32,269 --> 00:02:33,798
I’m still your friend,

29
00:02:35,115 --> 00:02:36,499
who genuinely cares about you.

30
00:02:44,887 --> 00:02:46,300
So you’re saying…

31
00:02:48,435 --> 00:02:52,600
that was our last time having sex?

32
00:02:57,900 --> 00:02:58,598
Mm.

33
00:03:07,829 --> 00:03:08,734
What a shame.

34
00:03:11,308 --> 00:03:12,795
I should’ve done better.

35
00:03:14,920 --> 00:03:16,198
It was already amazing.

36
00:03:35,810 --> 00:03:36,896
Thank you, Jack.

37
00:03:38,850 --> 00:03:40,031
Being your friend

38
00:03:44,942 --> 00:03:48,601
is better than
being nothing to you at all.

39
00:05:38,240 --> 00:05:39,600
Okay, a little more.

40
00:05:41,460 --> 00:05:42,580
Okay. That’s very good.

41
00:05:42,610 --> 00:05:43,696
That’s enough for today.

42
00:05:44,146 --> 00:05:44,965
Thank you.

43
00:05:52,317 --> 00:05:53,496
Don’t worry.

44
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:56,600
You look cool wearing that.

45
00:05:56,979 --> 00:05:58,503
Just think of it as an accessory.

46
00:05:59,026 --> 00:06:02,197
Now you’re the real Arnold,
a man of steel.

47
00:06:04,062 --> 00:06:04,995
Cool?

48
00:06:05,379 --> 00:06:07,540
I wish it really were just an accessory.

49
00:06:08,645 --> 00:06:11,902
I still don’t know
if I’ll ever fully use my ankle again.

50
00:06:19,465 --> 00:06:20,201
Hey.

51
00:06:22,860 --> 00:06:24,280
You can do it.

52
00:06:25,330 --> 00:06:27,804
That’s tomorrow’s problem.
Don’t worry about it yet.

53
00:06:30,070 --> 00:06:33,002
Don’t push it too hard.
It might get worse.

54
00:06:36,137 --> 00:06:36,897
That’s true.

55
00:06:38,680 --> 00:06:39,600
Smile.

56
00:06:41,425 --> 00:06:42,600
Let me see your smile.

57
00:06:44,028 --> 00:06:45,520
Come on, give me a smile.

58
00:06:45,792 --> 00:06:47,000
Smile.

59
00:06:50,454 --> 00:06:51,940
Your boyfriend’s taking care of you.

60
00:06:51,970 --> 00:06:53,400
Of course you’ll recover quickly.

61
00:06:57,127 --> 00:06:57,934
Good point.

62
00:07:00,081 --> 00:07:00,797
Hey.

63
00:07:01,990 --> 00:07:06,456
But I’m kind of nervous
about meeting your mom today.

64
00:07:08,149 --> 00:07:10,903
It’s my first time
meeting my boyfriend’s mom.

65
00:07:11,789 --> 00:07:14,299
What if she doesn’t like me?

66
00:07:15,269 --> 00:07:17,900
Tua, everyone likes you.

67
00:07:18,521 --> 00:07:21,000
Surely, my mom’s going to think
you’re adorable.

68
00:07:22,470 --> 00:07:23,748
How can you be so sure?

69
00:07:25,727 --> 00:07:28,897
Because I think you’re adorable,

70
00:07:29,590 --> 00:07:31,171
so my mom definitely will too.

71
00:07:31,715 --> 00:07:32,401
Really?

72
00:07:32,785 --> 00:07:33,282
Mm.

73
00:07:33,310 --> 00:07:34,945
See? Look how cute you are.

74
00:07:45,448 --> 00:07:46,202
Slowly.

75
00:07:48,967 --> 00:07:50,001
I’ll help you.

76
00:07:52,961 --> 00:07:55,001
-What’s wrong?
-I got dizzy. I feel weak.

77
00:07:55,586 --> 00:07:57,100
Hey. Seriously?

78
00:07:57,822 --> 00:07:59,700
I need an energy boost.

79
00:08:12,200 --> 00:08:13,762
Wow. I feel so strong now.

80
00:08:14,180 --> 00:08:15,170
Come on.

81
00:08:15,721 --> 00:08:16,426
Let’s go.

82
00:08:16,460 --> 00:08:17,247
Slow down.

83
00:08:20,400 --> 00:08:23,472
I took the job you got for me. It was fun.

84
00:08:24,020 --> 00:08:26,302
My friend told me to tell you
your music was amazing.

85
00:08:26,638 --> 00:08:28,570
Your schedule’s going to be packed
for a long time.

86
00:08:30,161 --> 00:08:31,197
Thank you so much.

87
00:08:31,700 --> 00:08:32,800
Don’t thank me.

88
00:08:33,170 --> 00:08:35,499
From now on,
I’ll be the one booking your gigs.

89
00:08:35,761 --> 00:08:36,850
So I can make money off you.

90
00:08:37,152 --> 00:08:38,045
Whoa.

91
00:08:39,500 --> 00:08:40,576
Young Master Raffy,

92
00:08:40,720 --> 00:08:42,697
since when did you become
this kind of person?

93
00:08:44,650 --> 00:08:45,872
Since I met you.

94
00:08:47,552 --> 00:08:48,460
Wow.

95
00:08:50,029 --> 00:08:50,810
Come on.

96
00:08:51,010 --> 00:08:53,579
Aren’t you supposed to maintain
the image of an actress’s son?

97
00:08:53,585 --> 00:08:55,130
You made a mess all over. Look.

98
00:08:55,562 --> 00:08:56,835
What a messy eater.

99
00:08:56,869 --> 00:08:58,835
Hello, handsome.

100
00:08:59,054 --> 00:09:00,900
-Yes?
-May I interview you two?

101
00:09:02,165 --> 00:09:02,900
Sure.

102
00:09:05,216 --> 00:09:06,579
Hi there.

103
00:09:06,608 --> 00:09:08,000
What are your names?

104
00:09:08,342 --> 00:09:09,300
I’m Rome.

105
00:09:10,155 --> 00:09:10,914
I’m Raffy.

106
00:09:11,034 --> 00:09:13,933
Today, we’re doing a fun little quiz.

107
00:09:13,960 --> 00:09:18,050
But I just saw you
wiping food off his mouth.

108
00:09:18,650 --> 00:09:20,262
Are you boyfriends?

109
00:09:20,438 --> 00:09:21,450
We’re friends.

110
00:09:21,484 --> 00:09:22,619
Friends.

111
00:09:24,531 --> 00:09:25,533
We’re boyfriends.

112
00:09:28,071 --> 00:09:30,645
Hey. Why are you lying?

113
00:09:31,040 --> 00:09:32,115
He likes joking around.

114
00:09:33,788 --> 00:09:34,602
So he’s joking?

115
00:09:34,896 --> 00:09:35,896
I’m telling the truth.

116
00:09:36,211 --> 00:09:39,194
We may not be boyfriends yet,
but we will be soon.

117
00:09:39,631 --> 00:09:40,303
Raffy.

118
00:09:41,284 --> 00:09:42,490
Since when was I your boyfriend?

119
00:09:42,577 --> 00:09:47,450
Well… I’ll let you two
figure that out first.

120
00:09:47,586 --> 00:09:49,004
But if you ask me,

121
00:09:49,029 --> 00:09:54,102
people with this kind of chemistry
always end up together.

122
00:09:55,413 --> 00:09:56,903
Will you excuse me?

123
00:09:57,081 --> 00:09:58,260
-Sure.
-Thank you.

124
00:10:02,457 --> 00:10:03,771
-Hey.
-Hm?

125
00:10:04,162 --> 00:10:07,308
When did I ever say
we were heading toward being boyfriends?

126
00:10:09,469 --> 00:10:10,601
That’s what you think.

127
00:10:11,272 --> 00:10:12,798
But this is what I think.

128
00:10:13,414 --> 00:10:15,287
I’m clearly pursuing you here.

129
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:17,500
When are you finally going to crack?

130
00:10:20,617 --> 00:10:22,000
Just keep being a messy eater.

131
00:10:22,085 --> 00:10:23,800
Hey, Rome!

132
00:10:25,933 --> 00:10:27,004
Wait for me.

133
00:10:31,780 --> 00:10:34,918
Arnold, I watched
the play recording you sent me.

134
00:10:35,902 --> 00:10:38,002
Steve and I really enjoyed it.

135
00:10:39,804 --> 00:10:41,520
You should’ve come see it live.

136
00:10:41,847 --> 00:10:43,001
It would’ve been even more fun.

137
00:10:43,188 --> 00:10:44,736
Tua did the costumes.

138
00:10:44,973 --> 00:10:46,604
Ah, great work.

139
00:10:47,302 --> 00:10:48,099
Thanks.

140
00:10:48,420 --> 00:10:51,530
So, are you Arnold’s friend
from university?

141
00:10:54,453 --> 00:10:55,297
No, Mom.

142
00:10:56,450 --> 00:10:57,475
He’s my boyfriend.

143
00:11:06,848 --> 00:11:12,339
In that case, thank you so much
for taking care of Arnold.

144
00:11:13,102 --> 00:11:16,899
He lives alone,
so I worry he might get lonely.

145
00:11:18,500 --> 00:11:20,995
Honestly, I don’t really
have to take care of him much.

146
00:11:21,140 --> 00:11:22,194
He’s amazing.

147
00:11:22,219 --> 00:11:23,700
He takes care of himself just fine.

148
00:11:25,493 --> 00:11:26,600
Eat up.

149
00:11:27,391 --> 00:11:28,099
Sure.

150
00:11:30,374 --> 00:11:35,050
So, have you thought about
what you want to do after graduation?

151
00:11:36,420 --> 00:11:38,007
Would you come live with me over there?

152
00:11:44,050 --> 00:11:46,754
We’re planning to open
a Thai restaurant in LA.

153
00:11:50,611 --> 00:11:54,004
Steve wants to open
a Thai restaurant in LA,

154
00:11:54,730 --> 00:11:58,496
and he wants you to come help out
and live with us there.

155
00:12:01,557 --> 00:12:02,891
I’m not sure yet, Mom.

156
00:12:02,915 --> 00:12:05,497
I still want to live here for now.

157
00:12:05,977 --> 00:12:07,001
Let me think about it first.

158
00:12:10,230 --> 00:12:13,897
But with your ankle injury,
being a dancer will be difficult.

159
00:12:14,740 --> 00:12:16,570
I really think
you should come live with me.

160
00:12:16,945 --> 00:12:20,201
Besides, this isn’t
just some casual invitation.

161
00:12:20,977 --> 00:12:23,140
This was actually Steve’s idea.

162
00:12:23,702 --> 00:12:28,096
He wants you to finally
come live with us as a family.

163
00:12:38,520 --> 00:12:40,200
How about this, Tua?

164
00:12:41,509 --> 00:12:43,700
Why don’t you go to LA with Arnold

165
00:12:43,997 --> 00:12:45,201
and live there together?

166
00:12:47,457 --> 00:12:48,201
Uh…

167
00:12:49,364 --> 00:12:50,247
I…

168
00:12:52,386 --> 00:12:52,811
I…

169
00:12:52,842 --> 00:12:53,602
Steve.

170
00:12:55,917 --> 00:12:59,000
I appreciate it,
but let me think about it. Okay?

171
00:12:59,545 --> 00:13:00,207
Sure.

172
00:13:00,525 --> 00:13:02,320
Whatever makes you and your mom happy.

173
00:13:04,140 --> 00:13:04,853
Thank you, Mom.

174
00:13:04,882 --> 00:13:05,548
Okay.

175
00:13:05,989 --> 00:13:07,647
Let’s eat.

176
00:13:09,210 --> 00:13:10,598
Here, have some more.

177
00:13:24,400 --> 00:13:25,100
Timmy.

178
00:13:25,900 --> 00:13:27,552
Did the doctor say you could drink?

179
00:13:27,832 --> 00:13:29,010
Slow down a little, will you?

180
00:13:29,656 --> 00:13:32,001
I injured my arm, not my liver.

181
00:13:32,620 --> 00:13:34,625
The rest of my organs
are perfectly fine too.

182
00:13:34,970 --> 00:13:35,998
I can drink.

183
00:13:36,200 --> 00:13:39,402
If he can still talk back like this,
just let him drink.

184
00:13:42,085 --> 00:13:42,798
See?

185
00:13:45,939 --> 00:13:48,195
You can’t pick that one. That’s cheating.

186
00:13:49,118 --> 00:13:50,737
I’m not cheating. That one’s allowed.

187
00:13:55,082 --> 00:13:56,737
If the game’s stressing you out this much,

188
00:13:57,930 --> 00:13:59,401
why don’t you just
come talk to me instead?

189
00:14:06,340 --> 00:14:07,303
Are you single?

190
00:14:07,669 --> 00:14:09,601
If you are, can I get your contact?

191
00:14:14,482 --> 00:14:15,503
My friend’s single.

192
00:14:16,360 --> 00:14:17,604
You two should exchange contacts.

193
00:14:20,106 --> 00:14:20,798
Excuse me.

194
00:14:21,706 --> 00:14:24,897
Judging from that reaction,
are you two boyfriends?

195
00:14:27,040 --> 00:14:28,002
We’re friends.

196
00:14:30,342 --> 00:14:33,937
Then would you accept my invitation
to come chat at my table?

197
00:14:50,219 --> 00:14:51,299
Hey, Dean.

198
00:14:52,040 --> 00:14:53,299
You really have changed.

199
00:14:53,794 --> 00:14:57,201
The old you would’ve picked a fight
with anyone who flirted with Jack.

200
00:14:57,648 --> 00:14:58,896
We worked things out.

201
00:14:59,460 --> 00:15:00,702
I’m not going to do that anymore.

202
00:15:01,110 --> 00:15:04,697
Then I can finally stop worrying,
now that you two are okay.

203
00:15:22,780 --> 00:15:24,500
Even if I’m not okay, I’ll have to be.

204
00:15:26,360 --> 00:15:27,798
Jack’s already made up his mind.

205
00:15:46,570 --> 00:15:50,201
Guys! Listen before you all
get too drunk to understand me.

206
00:15:50,510 --> 00:15:54,470
Let’s hear it for Tua
for shutting down his amusement park

207
00:15:54,500 --> 00:15:58,100
so we could have
our post-production party here!

208
00:15:58,124 --> 00:16:00,340
Whoo!

209
00:16:00,830 --> 00:16:01,650
And now,

210
00:16:02,014 --> 00:16:07,502
I’d like to invite our strict director,
Jack, to say a few words to the crew.

211
00:16:11,877 --> 00:16:14,742
We went through a lot
to make this project happen.

212
00:16:15,030 --> 00:16:17,697
The behind-the-scenes drama was
even more dramatic than the actual play.

213
00:16:18,240 --> 00:16:20,450
Don’t call yourself out like that.

214
00:16:21,524 --> 00:16:26,200
Anyway, thank you all so much
for being part of this success.

215
00:16:27,500 --> 00:16:30,450
Tonight, just have fun to the fullest.
I’ll take care of everyone.

216
00:16:30,694 --> 00:16:32,198
Wow.

217
00:16:32,429 --> 00:16:35,597
Then let’s get wasted!

218
00:16:53,487 --> 00:16:54,100
Rome.

219
00:16:56,488 --> 00:16:57,594
Thanks to you too.

220
00:16:59,008 --> 00:17:00,899
Even though you punched me
a bunch of times.

221
00:17:03,877 --> 00:17:05,320
Because you deserved every single one.

222
00:17:07,180 --> 00:17:11,411
Thank you too
for asking me to join this project.

223
00:17:11,940 --> 00:17:12,650
It was fun.

224
00:17:21,480 --> 00:17:24,037
So… what’s going on with you and Raffy?

225
00:17:25,811 --> 00:17:26,740
Why are you asking?

226
00:17:27,240 --> 00:17:28,303
You want him back now?

227
00:17:28,362 --> 00:17:29,370
It’s not like that.

228
00:17:29,850 --> 00:17:31,530
I already talked things through with him.

229
00:17:33,040 --> 00:17:34,497
I just want you to know…

230
00:17:34,930 --> 00:17:37,751
I’m rooting for you two.

231
00:18:10,376 --> 00:18:11,100
Jack.

232
00:18:12,470 --> 00:18:16,096
Thank you for choosing me
to be your Romeo.

233
00:18:19,130 --> 00:18:21,202
And I’m sorry for what happened.

234
00:18:25,020 --> 00:18:26,296
That’s all in the past now.

235
00:18:28,000 --> 00:18:29,897
I still feel bad about it anyway.

236
00:18:31,837 --> 00:18:34,604
What happened was my fault.

237
00:18:36,508 --> 00:18:37,539
It’s okay.

238
00:18:38,779 --> 00:18:40,502
I was part of the problem too.

239
00:18:41,240 --> 00:18:43,002
I pushed Dean
into doing the double casting,

240
00:18:43,026 --> 00:18:44,899
and everything spiraled from there.

241
00:18:46,856 --> 00:18:48,342
I can’t put all the blame on you.

242
00:18:54,010 --> 00:18:55,300
Since you mentioned it,

243
00:18:55,882 --> 00:18:58,370
Dean and I ended things on good terms.

244
00:18:59,896 --> 00:19:02,401
And you made up with Tua, right?

245
00:19:03,628 --> 00:19:05,496
There’s nothing left unresolved
between us anymore.

246
00:19:11,672 --> 00:19:13,600
But there’s still one thing unresolved.

247
00:19:18,614 --> 00:19:19,965
What the hell, Jack?

248
00:19:20,253 --> 00:19:21,943
Why do you suddenly want to go on a ride?

249
00:19:22,214 --> 00:19:24,201
Come on, just play with me.

250
00:19:24,761 --> 00:19:25,404
Come on.

251
00:19:25,894 --> 00:19:27,602
I’m not cleaning up your puke later.

252
00:19:37,540 --> 00:19:39,202
Put your safety gear on. Here.

253
00:19:47,336 --> 00:19:47,957
Dean.

254
00:19:51,620 --> 00:19:52,682
What are you doing?

255
00:19:52,823 --> 00:19:54,340
Jack, Arnold, what are you doing?

256
00:19:54,714 --> 00:19:56,268
You two need to sort things out.

257
00:19:56,402 --> 00:19:58,407
You made up with your boyfriend,
so now make up with your friend too.

258
00:19:58,432 --> 00:19:59,300
Got it?

259
00:20:00,075 --> 00:20:01,315
Don’t start the ride yet, sir.

260
00:20:01,780 --> 00:20:03,463
Keep them here until they make up.

261
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:32,499
I’m really sorry, Tua.

262
00:20:35,296 --> 00:20:36,099
You know?

263
00:20:38,250 --> 00:20:39,902
Ever since I moved out of your place,

264
00:20:42,340 --> 00:20:43,902
everything’s felt so weird.

265
00:20:47,650 --> 00:20:49,300
For the past four years,

266
00:20:51,688 --> 00:20:54,297
I’ve spent more time with you
than with my own family.

267
00:20:56,270 --> 00:20:57,934
I really loved university life.

268
00:20:59,693 --> 00:21:04,200
I got to discover acting,
the thing I love most,

269
00:21:05,210 --> 00:21:06,696
the boyfriend I loved most,

270
00:21:08,700 --> 00:21:10,201
and the friend I loved most.

271
00:21:15,420 --> 00:21:17,100
Without you in my life,

272
00:21:20,410 --> 00:21:21,697
I’m so fucking lost.

273
00:21:35,555 --> 00:21:37,496
Can we go back to being friends?

274
00:21:44,202 --> 00:21:45,480
You done talking?

275
00:21:50,977 --> 00:21:52,096
Now it’s my turn.

276
00:21:59,630 --> 00:22:00,899
You’re a fucking terrible friend.

277
00:22:06,976 --> 00:22:08,330
You’re not mad at me anymore, right?

278
00:22:10,420 --> 00:22:11,601
Holy shit, Tua!!

279
00:22:12,623 --> 00:22:14,302
Can I hug you now?

280
00:22:14,885 --> 00:22:15,702
Dean.

281
00:22:16,800 --> 00:22:18,204
Hey, you’re gonna break the ride.

282
00:22:18,937 --> 00:22:20,400
At least let me hug you first.

283
00:22:20,429 --> 00:22:21,503
Stay still.

284
00:22:22,040 --> 00:22:24,302
Sir, you can start the ride now.

285
00:22:25,277 --> 00:22:27,001
I made up with my friend already.

286
00:22:27,160 --> 00:22:28,293
I’m so happy.

287
00:22:28,788 --> 00:22:30,001
Will you stay still already?

288
00:22:30,035 --> 00:22:31,299
Can I get a hug?

289
00:23:21,034 --> 00:23:21,699
Hey.

290
00:23:22,438 --> 00:23:23,351
Are you drunk?

291
00:23:24,170 --> 00:23:25,102
A little.

292
00:23:26,090 --> 00:23:27,228
But I can still handle myself.

293
00:23:32,930 --> 00:23:34,397
So, are you finally giving in?

294
00:23:35,965 --> 00:23:36,700
Nope.

295
00:23:37,557 --> 00:23:40,395
Watching you chase after me like this
is way too satisfying.

296
00:23:40,585 --> 00:23:43,302
Hey, stop being such a pain.

297
00:23:44,654 --> 00:23:48,284
Nah. Someone like you
needs me to deal with you.

298
00:23:48,687 --> 00:23:50,939
And right now, I’m playing hard to get.

299
00:23:56,980 --> 00:23:58,580
So that’s the game you want to play?

300
00:24:11,520 --> 00:24:12,345
What are you doing?

301
00:24:12,451 --> 00:24:15,140
Oh, come on!

302
00:24:16,051 --> 00:24:17,211
What did you do?!

303
00:24:17,407 --> 00:24:18,402
What the?!

304
00:24:24,979 --> 00:24:26,897
Sorry for interrupting, everyone.

305
00:24:27,650 --> 00:24:29,500
But I have something important to say.

306
00:24:30,970 --> 00:24:32,736
I may not always be lovable.

307
00:24:35,146 --> 00:24:38,002
Actually, most of the time, I’m not.

308
00:24:40,370 --> 00:24:41,850
I’m not especially good at anything,

309
00:24:43,880 --> 00:24:45,801
and there’s nothing about me
that really stands out.

310
00:24:47,687 --> 00:24:51,801
But there’s one person who sees my worth.

311
00:24:58,370 --> 00:25:00,198
He knows how to handle me
when I’m stubborn.

312
00:25:05,207 --> 00:25:07,000
He helped me find my direction in life.

313
00:25:11,844 --> 00:25:13,100
Thank you so much, Rome.

314
00:25:17,693 --> 00:25:18,897
Like I said before,

315
00:25:20,794 --> 00:25:22,700
I’ll keep trying until you finally give in.

316
00:25:29,106 --> 00:25:30,100
Will you be my boyfriend?

317
00:25:32,840 --> 00:25:33,970
Gosh!

318
00:25:36,681 --> 00:25:38,265
Raffy, what are you doing?

319
00:25:38,302 --> 00:25:40,097
I’m embarrassed.

320
00:25:41,505 --> 00:25:42,597
I’m not.

321
00:25:43,920 --> 00:25:44,742
So?

322
00:25:46,069 --> 00:25:47,041
Yes or no?

323
00:25:47,078 --> 00:25:48,699
Say yes to him!

324
00:25:49,136 --> 00:25:50,472
Say yes.

325
00:25:50,508 --> 00:25:51,934
Boyfriend!

326
00:25:52,109 --> 00:25:52,874
Boyfriend!

327
00:25:53,065 --> 00:25:53,795
Boyfriend!

328
00:25:53,989 --> 00:25:54,777
Boyfriend!

329
00:25:54,880 --> 00:25:55,814
Boyfriend!

330
00:25:55,863 --> 00:25:56,739
Boyfriend!

331
00:25:56,937 --> 00:25:57,774
Boyfriend!

332
00:25:57,933 --> 00:25:58,773
Boyfriend!

333
00:25:58,927 --> 00:26:00,343
Boyfriend!

334
00:26:00,431 --> 00:26:02,102
Fine. I’ll be your boyfriend.

335
00:26:02,330 --> 00:26:03,945
Yay!

336
00:26:07,103 --> 00:26:10,395
Gosh, people in love are disgusting.

337
00:26:10,899 --> 00:26:15,002
You two can keep being all lovey-dovey,
but Rome, get back to the music.

338
00:26:15,610 --> 00:26:18,497
Us single people still want to dance.

339
00:26:20,285 --> 00:26:21,940
Come on. Hit the music.

340
00:26:22,408 --> 00:26:23,308
Alright.

341
00:26:30,282 --> 00:26:31,410
Ready to have some fun?

342
00:26:31,565 --> 00:26:33,296
Yes!

343
00:26:46,216 --> 00:26:47,142
Cute.

344
00:26:50,863 --> 00:26:51,890
Yeah, they are.

345
00:26:52,390 --> 00:26:53,890
But watching them
confess in front of everyone…

346
00:26:54,287 --> 00:26:56,410
made me cringe a little.

347
00:26:58,094 --> 00:26:59,997
I meant you. You’re cute.

348
00:27:01,022 --> 00:27:04,497
Wow, is this another couple happening?

349
00:27:05,069 --> 00:27:07,231
The stage boy has a crush on the producer.

350
00:27:08,980 --> 00:27:11,601
What is it with this play?
Everyone ends up together.

351
00:27:12,539 --> 00:27:14,100
Wait, are we going to end up together too?

352
00:27:15,995 --> 00:27:16,899
I’m kidding!

353
00:27:19,454 --> 00:27:20,210
That was sarcasm.

354
00:27:25,290 --> 00:27:26,737
You’re getting sneaky now.

355
00:27:27,640 --> 00:27:29,136
You planned all that with Jack.

356
00:27:30,274 --> 00:27:32,000
Guess I can’t trust you anymore.

357
00:27:35,170 --> 00:27:39,100
I got myself a boyfriend,
but you lost your friend.

358
00:27:39,761 --> 00:27:41,198
I can’t exactly be happy about that.

359
00:27:43,419 --> 00:27:44,902
I’m never going to lose him.

360
00:27:45,540 --> 00:27:47,699
Friends can never
completely cut each other off.

361
00:27:53,740 --> 00:27:54,496
Hey.

362
00:27:55,207 --> 00:27:56,797
You made up with him already.

363
00:27:57,180 --> 00:27:58,496
Why do you still look sad?

364
00:27:58,810 --> 00:28:00,500
Smile.

365
00:28:00,620 --> 00:28:02,899
Smile. Come on.

366
00:28:04,328 --> 00:28:05,198
Why are you sad?

367
00:28:06,137 --> 00:28:09,100
I’ve just been thinking about you.

368
00:28:09,610 --> 00:28:10,303
What?

369
00:28:10,688 --> 00:28:11,598
About me?

370
00:28:12,503 --> 00:28:13,699
Did I do something wrong?

371
00:28:14,651 --> 00:28:16,902
No. You didn’t do anything wrong.

372
00:28:18,382 --> 00:28:20,731
I’ve just been thinking about
what your mom said.

373
00:28:21,887 --> 00:28:24,800
So… are you really moving to LA?

374
00:28:31,220 --> 00:28:32,902
Honestly, I don’t want to go.

375
00:28:34,158 --> 00:28:37,200
But if I can’t find work
as an actor or dancer here,

376
00:28:38,230 --> 00:28:40,004
I might have to.

377
00:28:40,330 --> 00:28:41,648
Help out at the restaurant instead.

378
00:28:54,832 --> 00:28:56,103
But here’s what I think.

379
00:28:56,777 --> 00:29:00,343
If I really do go there,
I want to take you with me.

380
00:29:02,940 --> 00:29:04,595
But it’s not that simple.

381
00:29:06,048 --> 00:29:07,700
My family’s here.

382
00:29:08,616 --> 00:29:10,595
And my dream is here too.

383
00:29:11,280 --> 00:29:12,896
I still want to stay and work here.

384
00:29:16,112 --> 00:29:18,100
And you don’t want me to go, do you?

385
00:29:21,229 --> 00:29:22,402
Can you do that, though?

386
00:29:23,740 --> 00:29:25,398
I can’t even imagine

387
00:29:25,870 --> 00:29:28,900
how we’ll maintain
a long-distance relationship.

388
00:29:29,677 --> 00:29:31,099
Neither can I.

389
00:29:31,722 --> 00:29:35,402
That’s why I’m going to fight
as hard as I can for a future here.

390
00:29:41,568 --> 00:29:43,536
I want to live with you every day, Tua.

391
00:29:45,177 --> 00:29:47,602
I want to wake up
and kiss you every morning.

392
00:29:48,070 --> 00:29:50,152
I want to hold you
before bed every night.

393
00:29:51,940 --> 00:29:53,405
Kiss you every day.

394
00:29:53,840 --> 00:29:57,200
Take you out on my bike
and do everything together every day.

395
00:30:03,440 --> 00:30:07,097
Then from now on, I’ll fight for you too.

396
00:31:06,130 --> 00:31:07,450
Time really flies.

397
00:31:08,709 --> 00:31:11,597
Before we know it,
we’re graduating already.

398
00:31:12,063 --> 00:31:15,804
Mm. Four years were so short.

399
00:31:17,980 --> 00:31:21,496
But damn, we made
a lot of stories and memories.

400
00:31:26,657 --> 00:31:27,602
Honestly,

401
00:31:30,700 --> 00:31:33,202
I never thought
we’d ever have a day like this.

402
00:31:37,204 --> 00:31:38,745
A day where you and I don’t fight

403
00:31:39,675 --> 00:31:44,099
and can actually be real friends.

404
00:31:46,411 --> 00:31:51,800
Everything we went through together
was wilder than any roller coaster here.

405
00:31:58,794 --> 00:31:59,696
From now on,

406
00:32:01,143 --> 00:32:05,250
you and I are going our separate ways
to live our own lives.

407
00:32:07,240 --> 00:32:07,899
Mm.

408
00:32:07,982 --> 00:32:10,296
Who knows? Maybe in 10 or 20 years,

409
00:32:12,080 --> 00:32:13,903
we’ll find our way back
to each other again.

410
00:32:20,540 --> 00:32:24,962
But if you don’t look this good anymore,

411
00:32:27,360 --> 00:32:28,640
I’m not taking you back.

412
00:32:42,610 --> 00:32:43,253
Dean.

413
00:32:43,330 --> 00:32:44,100
Hm?

414
00:32:51,081 --> 00:32:53,000
You’re someone important in my life.

415
00:32:56,971 --> 00:32:58,450
You’ll always have a place right here

416
00:33:01,537 --> 00:33:02,903
in my heart.

417
00:33:09,440 --> 00:33:10,500
I love you, Jack.

418
00:33:16,832 --> 00:33:17,995
I love you too.

419
00:34:01,197 --> 00:34:01,897
Hello.

420
00:34:02,440 --> 00:34:05,131
(You’re flying back today?
Don’t ditch me.)

421
00:34:06,140 --> 00:34:07,499
I won’t.

422
00:34:07,961 --> 00:34:10,785
Unless my flight gets delayed,
I’ll be back in Bangkok this evening.

423
00:34:12,050 --> 00:34:12,742
Mm.

424
00:34:26,960 --> 00:34:27,897
See you guys later.

425
00:34:28,050 --> 00:34:28,900
Get home safe.

426
00:34:33,050 --> 00:34:33,699
See you.

427
00:34:34,453 --> 00:34:35,201
Bye.

428
00:34:48,878 --> 00:34:49,998
Do you need a hand?

429
00:35:14,682 --> 00:35:15,330
So…

430
00:35:17,030 --> 00:35:18,198
How’ve you been?

431
00:35:22,342 --> 00:35:23,103
Good.

432
00:35:24,448 --> 00:35:25,297
Tired.

433
00:35:26,253 --> 00:35:27,998
I just wrapped up my play tour.

434
00:35:30,454 --> 00:35:35,699
Hey, I shared your play
on my Story the other day.

435
00:35:39,850 --> 00:35:41,001
You’re amazing as always.

436
00:35:45,672 --> 00:35:46,497
What about you?

437
00:35:47,115 --> 00:35:47,770
Hm?

438
00:35:48,682 --> 00:35:49,699
How have you been?

439
00:35:51,314 --> 00:35:52,197
Good.

440
00:35:53,480 --> 00:35:55,120
Being a flight attendant pays pretty well.

441
00:35:56,263 --> 00:36:00,600
And on my days off,
I still go to auditions.

442
00:36:04,271 --> 00:36:08,200
I’m glad you still want to be an actor.

443
00:36:12,750 --> 00:36:17,598
But in the real world,
we need stable careers,

444
00:36:19,776 --> 00:36:22,802
so acting can only be
a side thing for now.

445
00:36:24,709 --> 00:36:27,398
Still, I think if you keep auditioning,

446
00:36:28,485 --> 00:36:30,197
you’ll become an actor someday.

447
00:36:30,750 --> 00:36:31,699
Trust me.

448
00:36:45,800 --> 00:36:47,050
Isn’t that Tua?

449
00:36:47,965 --> 00:36:49,097
Why aren’t you answering?

450
00:36:51,180 --> 00:36:53,330
I’m having dinner with him later.

451
00:36:54,060 --> 00:36:55,197
Do you want to join us?

452
00:37:02,370 --> 00:37:03,398
I don’t think so.

453
00:37:07,444 --> 00:37:08,602
I’ll see you later.

454
00:37:12,096 --> 00:37:12,851
Mm.

455
00:37:15,130 --> 00:37:16,200
See you later.

456
00:37:37,917 --> 00:37:40,200
Do you want to ditch Tua
and come with me instead?

457
00:38:05,530 --> 00:38:07,500
The Thai actor had an accident,

458
00:38:07,902 --> 00:38:09,900
so he couldn’t come.

459
00:38:10,604 --> 00:38:12,002
Oh, shit!

460
00:38:12,520 --> 00:38:14,629
This is your responsibility.

461
00:38:14,668 --> 00:38:17,197
You will solve this problem.

462
00:38:17,619 --> 00:38:19,328
I understand that, and I’m so sorry.

463
00:38:19,361 --> 00:38:20,400
You will solve this.

464
00:38:21,829 --> 00:38:23,308
Shit.

465
00:38:23,339 --> 00:38:24,502
What’s going on?

466
00:38:25,082 --> 00:38:27,282
The actor’s appendix ruptured.

467
00:38:27,309 --> 00:38:28,558
He can’t film today.

468
00:38:28,595 --> 00:38:30,997
Damn it.
This is my first international movie.

469
00:38:31,031 --> 00:38:32,299
It’s all ruined.

470
00:38:32,410 --> 00:38:34,700
Should we try
calling modeling agencies first?

471
00:38:35,280 --> 00:38:36,936
I already called everyone.

472
00:38:37,230 --> 00:38:39,497
It’s too last-minute.
Who’s even available right now?

473
00:38:39,702 --> 00:38:42,500
We need a man who speaks English,
around 180 centimeters tall,

474
00:38:42,530 --> 00:38:44,398
tanned, handsome, and with a six-pack.

475
00:38:44,670 --> 00:38:45,454
Damn it.

476
00:38:46,010 --> 00:38:47,496
It’s a motorcycle movie too.

477
00:38:47,690 --> 00:38:49,201
He needs to know how to ride.

478
00:38:49,580 --> 00:38:52,303
Where the hell am I supposed to find
a replacement? I’m not God.

479
00:38:54,296 --> 00:38:55,210
I’ve got someone.

480
00:38:56,731 --> 00:38:57,900
I know a guy.

481
00:39:11,050 --> 00:39:13,434
It has to be now?

482
00:39:13,520 --> 00:39:15,441
I’m in the middle of setting up
at Pink’s bar.

483
00:39:15,474 --> 00:39:16,602
Yes, right now.

484
00:39:16,817 --> 00:39:19,204
It’s an international film. Come on.

485
00:39:20,340 --> 00:39:20,995
But I…

486
00:39:21,146 --> 00:39:21,899
But?

487
00:39:22,558 --> 00:39:23,588
But what?

488
00:39:23,622 --> 00:39:24,697
There is no “but.”

489
00:39:24,838 --> 00:39:25,917
What are you afraid of?

490
00:39:26,321 --> 00:39:28,210
Just show the director what you can do.

491
00:39:28,305 --> 00:39:30,330
If he likes you,
you’ll start filming today.

492
00:39:31,734 --> 00:39:35,602
This is an audition for a major movie,
not some stage play.

493
00:39:35,640 --> 00:39:36,600
I’m nervous.

494
00:39:41,564 --> 00:39:43,398
I believe you can do it.

495
00:39:44,616 --> 00:39:46,130
Just like Romeo &amp; Romeo.

496
00:39:46,431 --> 00:39:48,700
I knew it had to be you.

497
00:40:02,050 --> 00:40:03,202
That’s your lucky charm.

498
00:40:04,674 --> 00:40:05,795
You’re getting this role.

499
00:40:07,882 --> 00:40:10,930
Tua, is your friend ready?

500
00:40:11,134 --> 00:40:12,450
I’ll take him to meet the director.

501
00:40:13,426 --> 00:40:14,200
Ready?

502
00:40:17,205 --> 00:40:19,601
I can’t wait to dress you as an actor.

503
00:41:00,100 --> 00:41:01,198
Can you sign this, please?

504
00:41:01,699 --> 00:41:02,499
Please sign this for us.

505
00:41:03,057 --> 00:41:04,234
Can we take a photo with you?

506
00:41:04,254 --> 00:41:04,900
Of course.

507
00:41:07,842 --> 00:41:09,398
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

508
00:41:15,840 --> 00:41:21,103
Choosing DJ Rome for this music festival
was definitely the right call.

509
00:41:21,413 --> 00:41:25,001
Honestly, when I first contacted you,
I didn’t think we’d be able to book him.

510
00:41:25,161 --> 00:41:28,297
Well, if it’s for a music festival,
we can make time for it.

511
00:41:28,690 --> 00:41:32,798
And that “DJing on a Tuk Tuk” content
got insanely high engagement.

512
00:41:32,990 --> 00:41:35,100
Our livestream pulled in a huge audience.

513
00:41:35,390 --> 00:41:36,902
Glad to hear that.

514
00:41:37,482 --> 00:41:39,644
Alright then,
see you on the day of the event.

515
00:41:39,671 --> 00:41:42,090
I’ll send Mr. Raffy all the details.

516
00:41:43,030 --> 00:41:43,580
Thank you.

517
00:41:43,611 --> 00:41:45,500
-Sounds good. Thank you so much.
-Thank you.

518
00:41:52,920 --> 00:41:54,702
So, how’s my schedule looking this year?

519
00:41:55,672 --> 00:41:57,500
You’re fully booked
all the way into next year.

520
00:41:57,728 --> 00:41:58,801
But don’t worry,

521
00:41:59,115 --> 00:42:01,100
I already scheduled some days off for you.

522
00:42:04,106 --> 00:42:07,601
You really know me well, Mr. Manager.

523
00:42:14,520 --> 00:42:15,401
Let me see.

524
00:42:18,229 --> 00:42:19,300
Looking good.

525
00:42:20,950 --> 00:42:22,450
Are you happy working with me?

526
00:42:23,579 --> 00:42:24,496
I am.

527
00:42:26,010 --> 00:42:28,294
Are you sure this is really your dream?

528
00:42:29,260 --> 00:42:31,102
Being an artist manager?

529
00:42:32,180 --> 00:42:34,297
You’re not just doing this
to support me, are you?

530
00:42:34,560 --> 00:42:35,357
Why?

531
00:42:35,970 --> 00:42:37,771
It’s not like there’s anything else
I want to do anyway.

532
00:42:37,810 --> 00:42:39,395
I like keeping an eye on my boyfriend,

533
00:42:39,580 --> 00:42:41,494
and watching him
become more and more successful.

534
00:42:44,103 --> 00:42:44,797
Okay.

535
00:42:48,745 --> 00:42:49,400
Oh.

536
00:42:49,580 --> 00:42:53,398
About those overseas music festivals,
nobody’s contacted us yet.

537
00:42:54,977 --> 00:42:58,899
I think I still need
a little more experience.

538
00:42:59,764 --> 00:43:00,691
That’s fair.

539
00:43:03,721 --> 00:43:05,402
Hey. How about this?

540
00:43:05,834 --> 00:43:08,401
After this event,
I’ll organize my own music festival.

541
00:43:09,758 --> 00:43:11,570
That way, we won’t have to
wait around for people to hire us.

542
00:43:11,982 --> 00:43:14,598
I’ll make you the headliner.

543
00:43:15,820 --> 00:43:16,700
Are you serious?

544
00:43:17,143 --> 00:43:18,100
Should we try it?

545
00:43:20,597 --> 00:43:22,702
Mm, I think it sounds exciting.

546
00:43:23,044 --> 00:43:25,290
If you believe we can do it,
then I believe we can too.

547
00:43:31,874 --> 00:43:34,490
This is the place
you used to bring me on dates.

548
00:43:35,768 --> 00:43:37,503
They turned it into a gallery now.

549
00:43:39,395 --> 00:43:40,703
Time flies. Everything changes.

550
00:43:42,940 --> 00:43:45,798
You mean this place or you and me?

551
00:43:47,271 --> 00:43:48,497
I mean everyone.

552
00:43:49,059 --> 00:43:50,497
People change every day.

553
00:43:53,915 --> 00:43:55,202
So how’s life going for you?

554
00:43:56,069 --> 00:43:58,502
Are you still with
that doctor boyfriend of yours?

555
00:44:03,072 --> 00:44:04,302
We broke up a long time ago.

556
00:44:05,440 --> 00:44:06,708
He was a doctor.

557
00:44:06,965 --> 00:44:10,303
He kept asking
why I bothered doing stage plays.

558
00:44:10,768 --> 00:44:12,050
Whether it even made enough money.

559
00:44:13,450 --> 00:44:15,001
He never really understood what I do.

560
00:44:21,040 --> 00:44:21,800
What about you?

561
00:44:22,300 --> 00:44:23,302
Are you seeing anyone?

562
00:44:24,837 --> 00:44:25,900
No, I’m not.

563
00:44:30,010 --> 00:44:32,397
I’ve been really busy. I fly all the time.

564
00:44:33,195 --> 00:44:34,602
I barely have time to date.

565
00:44:41,471 --> 00:44:43,702
Looking back,
we were pretty happy back then.

566
00:44:46,420 --> 00:44:50,001
We didn’t have to
worry about work or money.

567
00:44:52,510 --> 00:44:53,902
But I’m glad

568
00:44:55,470 --> 00:45:00,300
you’ve learned how to be happy
with the little things now.

569
00:45:01,508 --> 00:45:02,800
That’s way better than before.

570
00:45:05,678 --> 00:45:07,300
I guess I’ve become more mature.

571
00:45:09,070 --> 00:45:10,968
Things that used to upset me

572
00:45:12,506 --> 00:45:13,930
don’t really affect me anymore.

573
00:45:25,672 --> 00:45:29,398
But there’s still one thing I regret.

574
00:45:34,650 --> 00:45:35,502
What is it?

575
00:45:40,531 --> 00:45:41,500
Jeez, it’s raining.

576
00:46:06,939 --> 00:46:08,096
You’re all drenched.

577
00:46:08,870 --> 00:46:10,500
Want to go change at my place first?

578
00:46:44,745 --> 00:46:45,497
Uh…

579
00:46:46,675 --> 00:46:50,690
I’ll send this back to you
after I get it dry-cleaned.

580
00:46:53,260 --> 00:46:54,998
Or you could bring it back
to me yourself later.

581
00:46:55,358 --> 00:46:56,201
What?

582
00:46:58,040 --> 00:46:59,700
Are we never seeing
each other again after this?

583
00:47:44,277 --> 00:47:45,402
You’re hesitating.

584
00:47:46,954 --> 00:47:48,200
It’s not like you.

585
00:47:51,099 --> 00:47:52,294
Friends…

586
00:47:54,835 --> 00:47:56,102
don’t kiss.

587
00:47:57,520 --> 00:47:59,137
What if we got back together?

588
00:48:00,920 --> 00:48:02,100
Could we kiss then?

589
00:49:44,992 --> 00:49:47,899
In the end, you really became an actor,
and I get to dress you up.

590
00:49:48,210 --> 00:49:49,202
You’re very talented.

591
00:49:49,751 --> 00:49:50,696
Not really.

592
00:49:50,905 --> 00:49:53,500
I think it’s just because
my boyfriend got me the opportunity.

593
00:49:57,791 --> 00:49:58,499
Oh, hey.

594
00:49:59,392 --> 00:50:02,970
The casting lady asked me
to audition for another international film.

595
00:50:03,219 --> 00:50:03,991
Seriously?

596
00:50:04,022 --> 00:50:04,700
Yeah.

597
00:50:05,961 --> 00:50:08,802
So you’re really becoming
a famous actor now.

598
00:50:09,111 --> 00:50:09,899
That’s good.

599
00:50:10,561 --> 00:50:14,800
A famous costume designer
and a famous actor.

600
00:50:15,770 --> 00:50:17,099
We’re perfect for each other.

601
00:50:18,810 --> 00:50:20,400
If you get super famous,

602
00:50:20,644 --> 00:50:23,405
my dad’s definitely putting your standees
all over the amusement park.

603
00:50:25,380 --> 00:50:27,200
And when you win an Oscar,

604
00:50:28,150 --> 00:50:30,010
don’t forget to thank me in your speech.

605
00:50:30,754 --> 00:50:31,601
Whoa.

606
00:50:32,696 --> 00:50:33,502
That’s our deal?

607
00:50:34,819 --> 00:50:35,503
Fine.

608
00:50:46,705 --> 00:50:49,000
Thank you, everybody,
for being here tonight.

609
00:50:49,214 --> 00:50:50,702
I’m so grateful to be here.

610
00:50:50,826 --> 00:50:53,300
I just wanna say thank you to all my team,

611
00:50:53,623 --> 00:50:55,102
my friends and family.

612
00:50:55,672 --> 00:50:58,497
And most importantly, my boyfriend.

613
00:50:59,600 --> 00:51:01,802
My sweet, sweet boyfriend.

614
00:51:02,290 --> 00:51:03,097
Without him…

615
00:51:03,248 --> 00:51:05,595
So thank you to him. Good night.

616
00:51:08,414 --> 00:51:09,503
Alright, that’s enough.

617
00:51:09,990 --> 00:51:11,204
So? How was it?

618
00:51:11,880 --> 00:51:13,401
You’ve gotten really talkative lately.

619
00:51:41,102 --> 00:51:41,800
Hey.

620
00:51:43,447 --> 00:51:44,880
Hey, what are you doing?

621
00:51:45,613 --> 00:51:46,604
I miss you.

622
00:51:47,570 --> 00:51:49,490
We’ve been stuck on set
all the time lately.

623
00:51:49,820 --> 00:51:51,601
We barely get any time alone together.

624
00:51:59,430 --> 00:52:01,140
-Hey.
-What?

625
00:52:01,162 --> 00:52:02,500
Finish filming first.

626
00:52:02,971 --> 00:52:04,198
We can do this at home.

627
00:52:04,835 --> 00:52:06,305
Don’t you want a change of scenery?

628
00:52:07,444 --> 00:52:09,450
This is an actor’s private dressing room.

629
00:52:09,740 --> 00:52:10,832
No one’s gonna see.

630
00:52:49,480 --> 00:52:51,000
(Arnold, are you ready?)

631
00:52:51,260 --> 00:52:53,200
(We’ll be shooting in 10 minutes.)

632
00:53:06,976 --> 00:53:07,902
He’s ready.

633
00:53:24,804 --> 00:53:26,197
The stage layout looks good.

634
00:53:26,447 --> 00:53:28,100
And all the sponsors have responded.

635
00:53:28,230 --> 00:53:30,300
The only thing left now
is the artists’ contracts.

636
00:53:30,745 --> 00:53:32,296
Did you send all of them out yet?

637
00:53:32,457 --> 00:53:34,299
That’s already done.

638
00:53:34,500 --> 00:53:36,797
All that’s left is setting the date
for the contract signing.

639
00:53:36,859 --> 00:53:39,109
Wow. That was fast.

640
00:53:40,060 --> 00:53:43,804
So that means we can start promoting it
by the end of next month?

641
00:53:44,792 --> 00:53:45,503
That’s right.

642
00:53:47,377 --> 00:53:49,893
Let’s wait until all the partners arrive
so we can discuss everything at once.

643
00:53:49,973 --> 00:53:51,997
It’s been a while.

644
00:53:52,231 --> 00:53:53,690
How are they making you wait this long?

645
00:53:53,985 --> 00:53:55,204
I’m gonna have to wait.

646
00:53:55,665 --> 00:53:57,204
They’re important partners.

647
00:54:03,257 --> 00:54:04,902
Sorry, we’re late.

648
00:54:05,863 --> 00:54:06,693
Sorry, guys.

649
00:54:11,010 --> 00:54:12,437
Whoa.

650
00:54:13,410 --> 00:54:14,601
Did the meeting start already?

651
00:54:15,840 --> 00:54:17,103
We were waiting for you two.

652
00:54:17,530 --> 00:54:20,730
You own a company now
and you’re still late to meetings?

653
00:54:21,783 --> 00:54:23,001
Don’t blame Ray.

654
00:54:23,190 --> 00:54:24,200
It’s my fault.

655
00:54:24,950 --> 00:54:27,640
I was playing music late last night,
and he stayed with me the whole time.

656
00:54:27,666 --> 00:54:29,296
Wow.

657
00:54:29,710 --> 00:54:31,401
You two can’t be apart for a second, huh?

658
00:54:31,736 --> 00:54:34,100
Why? Don’t you trust Sand?

659
00:54:34,601 --> 00:54:37,402
It’s not Sand I don’t trust.
It’s everyone else.

660
00:54:37,790 --> 00:54:38,903
He’s my man.

661
00:54:40,564 --> 00:54:41,650
Nobody touches him.

662
00:54:42,360 --> 00:54:44,299
Jeez. You’re super jealous.

663
00:54:45,030 --> 00:54:47,465
I knew it. I’ve heard all about you.

664
00:54:47,500 --> 00:54:48,302
Rome!

665
00:54:50,377 --> 00:54:51,094
Rome.

666
00:54:52,408 --> 00:54:53,697
Aren’t we here to talk business?

667
00:54:54,160 --> 00:54:56,002
Stop asking them to gossip with you.

668
00:54:56,469 --> 00:54:57,798
Save that for the bar later.

669
00:54:59,497 --> 00:55:02,401
Alright then, Mr. CEO. Please continue.

670
00:55:03,557 --> 00:55:05,000
Why are you so grumpy?

671
00:55:06,669 --> 00:55:07,703
I’m scared.

672
00:55:11,456 --> 00:55:14,401
Now that everyone’s here,
I’ll continue the presentation.

673
00:55:15,297 --> 00:55:16,004
Mm.

674
00:55:28,785 --> 00:55:32,198
So your dream was to become a boss, right?

675
00:55:35,191 --> 00:55:36,997
When you boss people around,

676
00:55:38,922 --> 00:55:40,201
it’s so damn sexy.

677
00:55:41,820 --> 00:55:42,700
What are you doing?

678
00:55:43,798 --> 00:55:44,998
We’re in the office.

679
00:55:45,671 --> 00:55:46,850
An employee could walk in at any second.

680
00:55:47,031 --> 00:55:47,897
Even better.

681
00:55:48,645 --> 00:55:50,405
Two bosses loving each other

682
00:55:51,595 --> 00:55:53,099
means the company is stable.

683
00:55:57,310 --> 00:56:03,702
Do you remember
where we hooked up for the first time?

684
00:56:41,900 --> 00:56:43,237
We still have a meeting after this.

685
00:56:44,830 --> 00:56:46,149
You only have 15 minutes.

686
00:57:38,903 --> 00:57:40,998
Hey, what are you doing?

687
00:57:44,130 --> 00:57:45,100
I’m not telling you.

688
00:58:01,133 --> 00:58:02,299
I’m writing about us.

689
00:58:05,979 --> 00:58:07,001
Be serious.

690
00:58:07,657 --> 00:58:08,355
Mm.

691
00:58:09,390 --> 00:58:12,805
I’m writing a script based on our story.

692
00:58:14,560 --> 00:58:16,497
From the first day we met until now.

693
00:58:16,877 --> 00:58:19,000
We’ve been through so much,

694
00:58:19,983 --> 00:58:22,697
but in the end,
we found our way back to each other.

695
00:58:25,722 --> 00:58:26,594
What’s this?

696
00:58:26,626 --> 00:58:29,798
Are you writing another version
of Rome &amp; Romeo?

697
00:58:30,103 --> 00:58:34,096
So you’re going to write it,
direct it, and star in it yourself?

698
00:58:36,242 --> 00:58:36,899
Mm.

699
00:58:37,324 --> 00:58:38,900
I’ll write it, direct it,

700
00:58:40,870 --> 00:58:44,402
and give the lead role to my boyfriend.

701
00:58:49,270 --> 00:58:50,103
What do you think?

702
00:58:59,170 --> 00:59:02,998
Honestly, I think
you should cast someone else.

703
00:59:04,170 --> 00:59:05,797
There are plenty of talented actors
out there.

704
00:59:06,936 --> 00:59:07,601
I can’t.

705
00:59:08,890 --> 00:59:10,198
This role was written for you.

706
00:59:11,340 --> 00:59:12,703
You’re the only person who can play it.

707
00:59:20,320 --> 00:59:22,697
So?

708
00:59:23,420 --> 00:59:24,902
Will you take the role?

709
00:59:32,480 --> 00:59:33,397
I will.

710
00:59:37,510 --> 00:59:40,100
If I get to work under
such a talented director like you,

711
00:59:42,459 --> 00:59:43,798
I’ll do my best.

712
01:00:05,110 --> 01:00:10,100
Dean, you know that
no matter how much time passes,

713
01:00:13,080 --> 01:00:16,450
no one else can bring my ideas to life…

714
01:00:20,930 --> 01:00:22,349
as perfectly as you do.

715
01:00:29,190 --> 01:00:31,700
You’ll always be
my one and only favorite actor.

716
01:00:41,850 --> 01:00:42,801
Why are you crying?

717
01:00:46,500 --> 01:00:47,300
It’s nothing.

718
01:00:50,400 --> 01:00:51,699
You cry so easily now, huh?

719
01:01:14,528 --> 01:01:15,300
Thank you.

720
01:01:28,510 --> 01:01:30,410
So many of our friends
came to support us for opening night.

721
01:01:31,260 --> 01:01:32,398
Do your best.

722
01:01:33,110 --> 01:01:35,502
Yeah, but I’m a bit nervous.

723
01:01:36,600 --> 01:01:38,499
It’s been so long
since I last did a stage play.

724
01:01:41,160 --> 01:01:42,201
My hands are cold.

725
01:01:47,051 --> 01:01:48,204
You can do this.

726
01:01:53,340 --> 01:01:57,696
Thank you, Jack,
for still believing in me.

727
01:01:59,902 --> 01:02:01,197
Like I said,

728
01:02:02,390 --> 01:02:04,453
you’ve always been my number one actor.

729
01:02:11,897 --> 01:02:12,880
Break a leg.

730
01:02:13,324 --> 01:02:13,997
Mm.

731
01:03:06,800 --> 01:03:07,600
Excuse me.

732
01:03:08,450 --> 01:03:10,300
Mind if I sit here and watch with you?
